Claims Claims: 1 . A method performed by a computer system of a content service provider for executing a quality assurance and/or quality control (QA/QC) system module, the method comprising: performing at least one media verification procedure on a media content; and generating a QA/QC score based on results of the performed at least one media verification procedure; and determining if the media content satisfies a QA/QC standard based on the QA/QC score. 2. The method of Claim 1 , wherein media content comprises at least one of the following: digital video media; digital image media; and digital audio media. 3. The method of Claim 1 , wherein the performing of the at least one media verification procedure on the media content, comprises at least one of: confirming the media content contains a defined indication of a start of the media content and further contains a defined indication of an end of the media content; confirming the media content contains a forensic mark occurring in a defined time range when the media content is played out; confirming a set of language tracks contained in the media content satisfies a required set of language tracks; confirming a video component and an audio component of the media content are synchronized; confirming the media content contains a subtitle track synchronized to a corresponding audio track; and confirming the media content synopsis satisfies a defined rule. 4. The method of Claim 3, wherein the confirming that the media content contains the defined indication of the start of the media content and further contains the defined indication of the end of the media content, comprises: performing video frame extraction on the media content; processing the extracted frames through at least a start-content classifier and an end-credit classifier; and filtering the output of the processing through logical operations that confirm that the start of the media content and the end of the media content are present. 5. The method of Claim 4, wherein the confirming that the media content contains the defined indication of the start of the media content and further contains the defined indication of the end of the media content, further comprises: obtaining metadata identifying at least one of: indication of where end credits are expected to be located in the media content; background image characteristics expected in video frames of the media content containing end credits; and/or end credit text characteristics in video frames of the media content containing end credits; and adjusting parameter of the end-credit classifier based on the metadata before processing the extracted frames through at least a startcontent classifier and an end-credit classifier. 6. The method of Claim 5, further comprising: determining from the metadata, characteristics of how text is expected to move in video frames of the media content containing end credits and what text font is expected to be used in video frames of the media content containing end credits; and adjusting parameter of the end-credit classifier based on the metadata before processing the extracted frames through at least a startcontent classifier and an end-credit classifier. 7. The method of Claim 3, wherein the confirming the media content contains the forensic mark occurring in the defined time range when the media content is played out, comprises: performing video frame extraction on a portion of the media content corresponding to the defined time range; processing the extracted video frames through an optical character recognition (OCR) module and/or a machine learning mark identifier; and aggregating the output of the processing through logical operations that confirm that the forensic mark is present in the media content in the defined time range. 8. The method of Claim 3, wherein the confirming the media content contains the forensic mark occurring in the defined time range when the media content is played out, comprises: confirming the forensic mark remains displayed for at least a minimum time duration during playout of the media content. 9. The method of Claim 3, wherein the performing of the at least one media verification procedure on the media content, comprises: confirming the media content contains a first forensic mark and further contains a second forensic mark; and confirming that the first forensic mark is displayed concurrently with or within a threshold time of when the second forensic mark is displayed during playout of the media content. 10. The method of Claim 3, wherein the confirming the set of language tracks contained in the media content satisfies the required set of language tracks, comprises: extracting a set of audio tracks from the media content; 

 processing each of the extracted audio tracks in the set using a spoken language machine learning model adapted to identify defined types spoken languages; and aggregating the output of the processing through logical operations that confirm the set of language tracks contained in the media content satisfies the required set of language tracks. 11 . The method of Claim 10, further comprising: obtaining metadata identifying a set of expected spoken languages for the media content; and adjusting parameters of the spoken language machine learning model based on the metadata before processing each of the extracted audio tracks in the set using a spoken language machine learning model adapted to identify defined types spoken languages. 12. The method of Claim 3, wherein the confirming the set of language tracks contained in the media content satisfies the required set of language tracks, comprises: extracting a set of audio tracks from the media content; processing the extracted audio tracks in the set through a plurality of spoken language machine learning models each adapted to identify different types of spoken languages; and aggregating the output of the processing through logical operations that confirm the set of language tracks contained in the media content satisfies the required set of language tracks. 13. The method of Claim 1 , further comprising: extracting from the media content a first chunk having a first duration; performing the at least one media verification procedure on only the first chunk of the media content; 

 generating a first QA/QC score based on results of the performed at least one media verification procedure on only the first chunk of the media content; determining if the media content satisfies a QA/QC standard based on the first QA/QC score; and responsive to determining the media content does not satisfy the QA/QC standard based on the first QA/QC score, further performing extracting from the media content a second chunk having a second duration that is greater than the first duration, performing the at least one media verification procedure on only the second chunk of the media content, generating a second QA/QC score based on results of the performed at least one media verification procedure on only the second chunk of the media content, and determining if the media content satisfies the QA/QC standard based on the second QA/QC score. 14. The method of Claim 13, responsive to determining the media content does not satisfy the QA/QC standard based on the second QA/QC score, further comprising: extracting from the media content a third chunk having a third duration greater than the second duration; performing the at least one media verification procedure on only the third chunk of the media content; generating a third QA/QC score based on results of the performed at least one media verification procedure on only the third chunk of the media content; and determining if the media content satisfies the QA/QC standard based on the third QA/QC score. 15. The method of Claim 1 , further comprising: 

 extracting from the media content a first chunk corresponding to a first window location within the media content; performing the at least one media verification procedure on only the first chunk of the media content; generating a first QA/QC score based on results of the performed at least one media verification procedure on only the first chunk of the media content; determining if the media content satisfies a QA/QC standard based on the first QA/QC score; and responsive to determining the media content does not satisfy the QA/QC standard based on the first QA/QC score, further performing extracting from the media content a second chunk corresponding to a second window location within the media content that at least partially does not overlap the first window location within the media content, performing the at least one media verification procedure on only the second chunk of the media content, generating a second QA/QC score based on results of the performed at least one media verification procedure on only the second chunk of the media content, and determining if the media content satisfies the QA/QC standard based on the second QA/QC score. 16. The method of Claim 15, responsive to determining the media content does not satisfy the QA/QC standard based on the second QA/QC score, further comprising: extracting from the media content a third chunk corresponding to a third window location within the media content that is time shifted by a threshold time duration away from the second window location and which does not overlap either of the first and second window locations within the media content; 

performing the at least one media verification procedure on only the third chunk of the media content; generating a third QA/QC score based on results of the performed at least one media verification procedure on only the third chunk of the media content; determining if the media content satisfies the QA/QC standard based on the third QA/QC score.
